The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                Air India reintroduced a Calcutta-Bagdogra flight on September 1. The flight leaves Calcutta on Tuesdays, Thursdays and Saturdays at 1.05pm and reaches Bagdogra at 2pm. The return flight leaves Bagdogra at 2.40pm and arrives in Calcutta at 3.35pm. The airline will operate extra flights on the route between September 14 and November 9 to cater to the festive rush. The additional flight, on Wednesdays and Sundays, will take off from Calcutta at 2pm and reach Bagdogra at 2.55pm. The return flight will take off at 3.35pm and reach Calcutta at 4.30pm. Air India will also restore operations between Calcutta and Yangon from October 3, on Mondays and Fridays.    A drunk passenger was offloaded from an Air India flight and detained at Calcutta airport police station on Monday for shouting at co-passengers and cabin crew. Lalhmachhuama, in his 20s, had boarded the airlines Calcutta-Delhi flight, which was scheduled to take off at 5.05pm.    NRS Medical College and Hospital will have to maintain a performance record of doctors and audit analysis of patients who die. The decision was taken at a meeting health minister Surjya Kanta Mishra and tourism minister Manab Mukherjee held with the hospital authorities on Monday. Mukherjee is chairman of the hospitals patient welfare committee. The authorities will also have to maintain records of the number of surgeries performed and the number of patients attended by doctors.    A fire broke out on the third floor of the Customs house on Strand Road on Monday morning. A short circuit caused the blaze, which was doused by two fire tenders in half an hour. No one was injured.    Shankar Prasad Suman, 50, a schoolteacher, was found dead in his Topsia house on Monday afternoon. Police broke open the door after being informed by Sumans neighbours. The teachers body has been sent for post-mortem.                                                                                                                                                              
